{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, Tofacitinib has been reported to decrease rapamycininduced autophagy 53, which may raise concerns for AD therapy, as increased autophagy has been associated with enhanced cognitive function 54.",
    "However, it is important to consider the stage-specific context of AD.",
    "As noted with rapamycin later, excessive autophagy may have detrimental outcomes in the later stage.",
    "Therefore, JAK inhibitors could be clinically relevant as part of a tailored therapeutic strategy to balance autophagy modulation depending on disease progression.",
    "Of the remaining two candidates, Niraparib is a protein poly (ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) inhibitor, and Palbociclib is a cyclin-dependent kinase (CDK)4/6 inhibitor."
  ]
}